label: atrioventricular nodal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the right coronary artery and supplies the atrioventricular node.
synonym: atrioventricular node branch of right coronary artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: subsegmental pulmonary artery
definition: An artery that is a branch of the segmental pulmonary artery and supplies deoxyge blood to a smaller subsegment of the lung.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: thyrocervical trunk
definition: An artery that branches from the subclavian artery and supplies the thyroid gland, neck, and upper back regions.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: septal perforating artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left anterior descending artery and supplies the interventricular septum of the heart.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: posterolateral artery
definition: An artery that branches from the right coronary artery or the circumflex artery and supplies the posterior and lateral walls of the left ventricle.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: pulmonary arteriole
definition: An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteries and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries and alveolar capillaries of the lungs.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: ascending pharyngeal artery
definition: An artery of the neck that branches from the external carotid artery and supplies the pharynx.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: dural artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal carotid artery and supplies the anterior clinoid process of the dura mater.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: pericardial artery
definition: An artery that branches from the descending thoracic aorta and supplies the dorsal portion of the pericardium.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: percardiacophrenic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal thoracic artery and supplies the pericardium and the diaphragm.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: incisor artery
definition: An artery that branches from the inferior alveolar artery and supplies the roots and pulp of the teeth of the lower jaw. It forms anastomoses with its contralateral partner.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: intra-acinar arteriole
definition: An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteriole and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries in the alveoli of the lungs.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: ascending palatine artery
definition: An artery that branches from the facial artery, and branches to supply the soft palate and the palatine tonsil.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: submental artery
definition: An artery that branches from the facial artery that runs forward under the mouth, then turns upward upon reaching the chin.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: deep lingual artery
definition: An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies blood to the tongue itself, particularly the body and tip of the tongue. The deep lingual artery travels superiorly in a tortuous course along the under (ventral) surface of the tongue, below the longitudinalis inferior, and above the mucous membrane.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: dorsal lingual artery
definition: An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies the soft palate, tonsils, epiglottis, palatoglossal arch, and adjacent mucous membrane. The dorsal lingual artery runs along the upper border of the hyoid bone and anastomises with its fellow of the opposite side.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: accessory meningeal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the meninges. The accessory meningeal artery ascends through the foramen ovale to enter the cranial cavity and supply the dura mater of the floor of the middle cranial fossa and of the trigeminal cave, and to the trigeminal ganglion.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: artery of pterygoid canal
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies blood to structures in the auditory tube, tympanic cavity, and upper pharynx. The artery of the pterygoid canal courses through the pterygoid canal, a small bony canal located in the sphenoid bone of the skull.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: descending palatine artery
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the hard and soft palate.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: left anterior descending artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left coronary artery and supplies the anterior wall of the left ventricle, the interventricular septum, and the apex of the heart.
synonym: anterior interventricular branch of left coronary artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: anterior humeral circumflex artery
definition: An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, biceps brachii, and coracobrachialis muscles, the glenohumeral joint, the proximal humeral head, and the skin overlying the anterior aspect of the proximal humerus. This artery courses laterally across the anterior surface of the humerus and anastomoses with the posterior humeral circumflex artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: posterior humeral circumflex artery
definition: An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, teres major, teres minor, and long and lateral heads of the triceps brachii muscles, glenohumeral joint, and the cutaneous supply to the area posterolateral to the proximal humerus. This artery courses posteriorly with the axillary nerve, through the quadrangular space, to the posterior aspect of the humerus and anastomoses with the anterior humeral circumflex artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: anterior ciliary artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the anterior segment of the eyeball and ciliary body.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: short posterior ciliary artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the choroid and ciliary processes.
synonym: Set of short posterior ciliary arteries|Short posterior ciliary arteries
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: long posterior ciliary artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the choroid, ciliary body and iris.
synonym: Set of long posterior ciliary arteries|Long posterior ciliary arteries
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: right marginal artery
definition: An artery that is a branch of the right coronary artery. It follows the acute margin of the heart supplying blood to the right ventricle.
synonym: Marginal branch of right coronary artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: segmental renal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the renal artery. The anterior division of the renal artery typically divides into four segmental arteries, whereas the posterior division of the renal artery supplies one segmental artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: superior segmental renal artery
definition: A segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, superiorly and laterally. It supplies the superior (apical) lobe of the kidney.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: anterior superior segmental renal artery
definition: A segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, superiorly and laterally towards the superior pole of the kidney. It does not ascend as steeply as the superior segmental artery and does not extend into the superior pole. It supplies the anterosuperior lobe of the kidney, which includes the central anterosuperior region, extending to the lateral aspect and slightly onto the posterior surface of the kidney.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: anterior inferior segmental renal artery
definition: A segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, laterally and angled slightly inferiorly. It supplies the anteroinferior lobe of the kidney, which includes the central anteroinferior region, extending to the lateral aspect and slightly onto the posterior surface of the kidney.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: inferior segmental renal artery
definition: A segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, inferiorly and laterally towards the inferior pole of the kidney. It supplies the inferior lobe of the kidney, which encompasses the whole of the inferior pole of the kidney, including the anterior and posterior surfaces.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: posterior segmental renal artery
definition: A segmental renal artery that passes posterior to the renal pelvis and travels laterally, more or less horizontally. It supplies the posterior lobe of the kidney, which includes all of the central-posterior surface of the kidney. This excludes the superior and inferior poles and a small posterolateral portion.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: dorsal pancreatic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the head, uncinate process, neck, body and tail of the pancreas. It anastamoses with the superior pancreaticoduodenal artery.
synonym: Dorsal pancreatic part of splenic artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: greater pancreatic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the left half of the body and tail of the pancreas.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: caudal pancreatic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the tail of the pancreas.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: transverse pancreatic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the dorsal pancreatic artery and supplies the body and tail of the pancreas. It is also known as the inferior pancreatic artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: anterior superior pancreaticoduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the first and second parts (superior and descending parts) of the duodenum and the head of the pancreas.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: posterior superior pancreaticoduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the first and second parts of the duodenum, distal common bile duct and head of the pancreas.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: anterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery. It courses on the anterior surface of the uncinate process continuing on to the head of the pancreas. It supplies the uncinate process, head of the pancreas, and the second and third parts of the duodenum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: posterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery. It courses posterior to the uncinate process and head of the pancreas. It supplies uncinate process and head of the pancreas, second and third parts of the duodenum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: anterior cecal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the anterior portion of the cecum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: posterior cecal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the posterior portion of the cecum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: colic branch of ileocolic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the cecum and inferior portion of the ascending colon.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: marginal artery of Drummond
definition: An arterial arcade that connects the superior and inferior mesenteric arteries and supplies the colon.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: ascending branch of left colic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left colic artery and supplies the superior portion of the descending colon, the left colic flexure, and the right one half to one third of the transverse colon.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: descending branch of left colic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left colic artery and supplies the inferior portion of the descending colon.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: meandering mesenteric artery
definition: An artery that is a collateral pathway linking the superior and inferior mesenteric arteries and supplies the colon.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: left artery of caudate lobe
definition: An artery that branches from the left hepatic artery and supplies the medial portion of the caudate lobe of the liver.
synonym: Caudate lobe branch of left hepatic artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: right artery of caudate lobe
definition: An artery that branches from the right hepatic artery and supplies the lateral portion of the caudate lobe of the liver.
synonym: Caudate lobe branch of right hepatic artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: cutaneous branch of ulnar artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ulnar artery and supplies the medial aspect of the forearm, medial aspect of the wrist, and to the region surrounding the hypothenar eminence.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: ileal branch of ileocolic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the distal most ileum, ileocecal junction, cecum and appendix.
synonym: Ileal branch of inferior branch of ileocolic artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: retroduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the posterior surface of the proximal duodenum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: supraduodenal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the superior, right, and anterior surfaces of the first part of the duodenum, extending into the second part.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: right gastric artery
definition: An artery that branches from the proper hepatic artery and supplies the right side of the lesser curvature of the stomach and adjacent anterior and posterior surfaces.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: short gastric artery
definition: An artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the fundus of the stomach on the side of the greater curvature of the stomach.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: lobar artery of spleen
definition: An artery that branches from the splenic artery at the splenic hilum at which it divides into one or two terminal branches supplying a lobe of the spleen.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: esophageal branches of left gastric artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left gastric artery and supplies the abdominal esophagus.
synonym: Esophageal part of left gastric artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: posterior scrotal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal pudendal artery and supplies the scrotum.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744

label: vaginal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal iliac artery and supplies the lower vagina and fundus of the bladder.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744
